* Current beach town residents are asking themselves if they can afford to keep their homes due to the increase insurance rates.  In today's economy, this is a major financial setback for all us trying to hold on.  The problem is that we folks living in beach towns are stuck between a rock and a hard place.  We would not be able to sell our homes because no one is buying.  So, we are stuck.  We have no choice but to buckle up and pay.
