The NC Coast belongs to all of us.  I do not own property at the beach, but property owners at the beach should not bear the entire burden for damages that have been incurred as the result of various storms.  These storms have caused damages to many areas around the state, not just to beach properties.  It is simply not appropriate to target insurance rate increases only to beach property owners. 

Any insurance rate increases should be reviewed and dealt with on a statewide basis, in an equitable manner, when rate increases relate to an area that is clearly a benefit to the entire state. 

Approval of Senate Bill 6 and/or House Bill 26 should provide an opportunity for public debate on this matter. Thank you.


